  "summary": "Today is 28-03-2026.\n\n## ðŸ”‘ Executive Summary\n*   Google expands Gemini 3.1 with specialized audio, image, and efficient models, integrating AI across its products.\n*   Axiom Math launched Axplorer, an AI tool to discover new mathematical patterns, aiming to revolutionize scientific research.\n*   A battery company pivoted to AI materials discovery, highlighting AI's growing role in industrial R&D and sustainability.\n*   Pentagon's ban on Anthropic was halted, signaling ongoing regulatory challenges and policy complexities for major AI firms.\n*   Agentic commerce demands robust data management for trust and scalable autonomous transactions, emphasizing \"truth and context.\"\n\n## ðŸš€ Top Stories\n\n### Google Unleashes Specialized Gemini 3.1 Models and Expands AI Integrations\nGoogle released Gemini 3.1 Flash Live for natural audio AI and Lyria 3 for music generation, alongside Nano Banana 2 for image editing. These models are rapidly integrating across Google products like Search, Translate, and Sheets, enhancing user experience and developer capabilities.\nSource: Google AI Blog\nLink: [https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/models-and-research/gemini-models/gemini-3-1-flash-live/](https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/models-and-research/gemini-models/gemini-3-1-flash-live/) (and related Google AI Blog posts for Lyria 3, Nano Banana 2)\n\n### AI Startup Axplorer Aims to Redefine Mathematical Discovery\nAxiom Math released Axplorer, a free AI tool designed to discover novel mathematical patterns, moving beyond solving existing problems to generating new ideas. This initiative aligns with DARPA's push for AI in mathematics, promising breakthroughs with broad technological impact.\nSource: MIT Technology Review - AI\nLink: [https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/03/25/1134642/this-startup-wants-to-change-how-mathematicians-do-math/](https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/03/25/1134642/this-startup-wants-to-change-how-mathematicians-do-math/)\n\n